  answer: 'Sight reading means playing music you have never seen before, straight through, without stopping. To practise it, choose something considerably easier than your current pieces, look through it before you start, set a slow steady pulse, and never go back to correct a mistake. Ten minutes a day of easy material beats an hour of hard material.',
